pygments: Pygments (syntax highlighting package written in Python)
pygments:
pygments: Pygments is a generic syntax highlighter for general use in all
pygments: kinds of software such as forum systems, wikis or other
pygments: applications that need to prettify source code. Feature highlights:
pygments: 
pygments:   * a wide range of common languages and markup formats is supported;
pygments:   * special attention is paid to details, increasing quality by a
pygments:     fair amount;
pygments:   * support for new languages and formats are added easily;
pygments:   * a number of output formats, presently HTML, LaTeX, RTF, SVG, all
pygments:     image formats that PIL supports and ANSI sequences;
pygments:   * it is usable as a command-line tool and as a library;
pygments:
pygments: Packaged by Georgi D. Sotirov <gdsotirov@gmail.com>
